               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184205090052"></xptr>
               <p>Islington. On the 9th of April the prisoner came to my shop—I did not see him take the loaves—they were brought back.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420509-name-383" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420509-name-383" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420509-name-383" type="surname" value="HANNEY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420509-name-383" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM HANNEY</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Elder-walk. Between seven and eight o'clock this evening I saw the prisoner take two loaves of bread from the prosecutor's shop, and give them to another boy—they stood under the window—I told the prosecutor a quarter of an hour after—I am quite sure I saw the prisoner take them.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I did not take them.</p>
